1
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:38,289
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,280
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:53,789 --> 00:01:54,590
Go over there!

4
00:01:56,890 --> 00:01:57,690
Go over there!

5
00:02:15,490 --> 00:02:16,010
I heard

6
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:17,910
his son is head over heels in debt.

7
00:02:18,270 --> 00:02:20,240
I heard
he even sold his house in the city.

8
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,010
I heard his daughter

9
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:22,570
also came back with a huge debt.

10
00:02:22,570 --> 00:02:24,240
What a terrible tragedy.

11
00:02:25,230 --> 00:02:26,690
Anything else new lately?

12
00:02:28,730 --> 00:02:29,840
What's going on?

13
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,250
Why are we out of gas?

14
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:34,950
Chen Fan, you went the wrong way,
didn't you?

15
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:36,240
Look at the map.

16
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:38,410
This isn't the place.

17
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,760
Can our car still run?

18
00:02:40,780 --> 00:02:42,110
We're screwed.

19
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:43,570
We can't be stuck here,

20
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:45,680
and we definitely can't spend the night
here.

21
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,280
In the end, you still need me.

22
00:02:47,930 --> 00:02:48,730
You have a way?

23
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:52,750
Shan.

24
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:55,120
Our car ran out of gas.

25
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,850
We're in the middle of nowhere.

26
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,010
What should we do?

27
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,620
Send me your location quickly.

28
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:00,470
Wait for me on the road.

29
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:01,730
-I'm coming to pick you up.
-Okay. Thank you, Shan.

30
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:03,460
I'll send you the location now.

31
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,230
I'm so thirsty.

32
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,320
Take out the drinks.

33
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,010
No, no.

34
00:03:08,210 --> 00:03:09,210
These are for Ning.

35
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:10,010
No one is allowed to drink them first.

36
00:03:10,010 --> 00:03:10,560
Who...

37
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,360
Whoever touches them

38
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,090
is a traitor.

39
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,050
You're so mean!

40
00:03:14,170 --> 00:03:15,080
We're dying of thirst,

41
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,510
and you still won't let us drink!

42
00:03:16,510 --> 00:03:17,930
Open the car door!

43
00:03:17,930 --> 00:03:18,800
Don't run!

44
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,050
There are fruits!

45
00:03:25,090 --> 00:03:26,350
Let's pick some to eat!

46
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,890
This one isn't ripe yet, is it?

47
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:40,160
I want the biggest one.

48
00:03:44,210 --> 00:03:46,360
You're really treating me like Guowei?

49
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:46,770
Move aside.

50
00:03:46,770 --> 00:03:47,770
I'll do it myself.

51
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,300
Come on.

52
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,300
Be careful.

53
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,600
I can't reach it.

54
00:04:17,610 --> 00:04:18,820
Go a bit higher.

55
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,000
It hurts!

56
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,760
What are you two doing?

57
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:40,950
Thank god you broke my fall.

58
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:41,820
Thanks.

59
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,210
We were picking fruits!

60
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,610
Chen Fan, are you gonna pick some or not?

61
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:54,150
If you don't,

62
00:04:54,150 --> 00:04:55,800
I'll drink all the drinks in your car.

63
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,400
I'll pick.

64
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,760
Look at you.

65
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:15,240
You don't even rest during summer break.

66
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,300
You don't need

67
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,880
to do these chores.

68
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,440
Just having you here with me

69
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,680
is more than enough to make me happy.

70
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:34,930
Grandma.

71
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:37,220
The two of us can't possibly finish

72
00:05:37,230 --> 00:05:38,240
such a big pot, can we?

73
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:40,800
Go to the village committee
and see who's there.

74
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,120
Invite them all over
for some mung bean soup.

75
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,980
It's more fun with people around.

76
00:05:46,290 --> 00:05:47,000
Grandma,

77
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,409
you have some first.

78
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:53,930
Go.

79
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:55,409
Go.

80
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:10,680
Who are you people?

81
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,210
You're stealing my fruits!

82
00:06:13,170 --> 00:06:14,940
How could you pick so many?

83
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:15,880
This...

84
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,070
Village Chief!

85
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:21,050
These people showed up out of nowhere.

86
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:23,080
They picked a whole load of fruits
from my tree

87
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:24,670
and even damaged the branches!

88
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:26,270
Everyone, be the judge here!

89
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:28,120
So they're thieves stealing things.

90
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,050
I say let it go.

91
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,610
It's not your tree.
Of course you'd say that.

92
00:06:30,610 --> 00:06:31,440
Ma'am,

93
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:33,420
we really didn't know these fruits

94
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:34,680
belonged to you.

95
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:35,880
Ma'am?

96
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,560
You...

97
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,440
Who are you calling Ma'am?

98
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,560
Miss.

99
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,930
How about this?

100
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,230
You name your price.

101
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:44,930
We'll pay full price,

102
00:06:44,930 --> 00:06:45,810
or even double.

103
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,560
-You think money can solve everything?
-You think money can solve everything?

104
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,680
Ma'am.

105
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,800
Miss.

106
00:06:55,930 --> 00:06:57,360
We've already apologized

107
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,440
and said we'll pay for it.

108
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:58,930
You...

109
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,440
What more do you want?

110
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:02,550
What's with that attitude?

111
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:03,680
You think apologizing

112
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,810
and paying up makes everything right?

113
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:06,560
Then...

114
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,760
Just let it go.

115
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,090
What do you want us to do?

116
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,440
You're the only one here

117
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,300
talking sense.

118
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:15,680
I'm furious.

119
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,240
Village Chief, you tell me.

120
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,360
How should this be handled?

121
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,240
I say let it go.

122
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,120
Ning.

123
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:24,800
Aunt.

124
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:27,190
They are my high school classmates.

125
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,780
They definitely didn't know

126
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:30,280
the fruit trees belonged to someone.

127
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,040
Otherwise,

128
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,640
they wouldn't have damaged the branches.

129
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,500
Just take their money and move on.

130
00:07:36,170 --> 00:07:37,159
How come Luo Ningzi has

131
00:07:37,159 --> 00:07:37,960
such an aunt?

132
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,680
I don't know.

133
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:40,650
My grandma made

134
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,000
mung bean soup for everyone back home.

135
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,440
Why don't we go drink some mung bean soup,

136
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,159
cool down a bit,

137
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:45,380
and then figure out what to do.

138
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:46,230
I'm not going!

139
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,970
This is really out of line.

140
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:48,970
Or how about this?

141
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,460
We can help you

142
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,360
with some work.

143
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,420
We can do anything.

144
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:53,409
Work?

145
00:07:54,070 --> 00:07:54,930
What can you do?

146
00:07:55,030 --> 00:07:56,210
Look at your skinny little arms and legs.

147
00:07:56,210 --> 00:07:57,450
What can you do?

148
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,240
No way.

149
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,490
You're joking.

150
00:08:00,490 --> 00:08:01,880
You're

151
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,880
all grown-ups.

152
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,680
Why are you so hard on these kids?

153
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:06,380
Come home with me, all of you.

154
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:08,680
I'm not going.

155
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,000
-Enough.
-Yaogu.

156
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,000
Come back with me
and have some mung bean soup.

157
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,560
Alright. Go home.

158
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,240
Just go home.

159
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:13,800
Go home, everyone.

160
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,320
Break it up!

161
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:14,680
Go home!

162
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,240
Go home!

163
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:15,800
Go home!

164
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,490
Go home for dinner!

165
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:17,320
Alright.

166
00:08:17,350 --> 00:08:18,320
Everyone, go home!

167
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:18,800
Ning.

168
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:20,860
Why didn't you reply to my messages?

169
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:22,200
You didn't pick up my calls either!

170
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:22,950
Luo Ningzi,

171
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,440
how can you have an aunt like that?

172
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,120
She was describing us
as skinny arms and legs?

173
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,780
She was calling us weaklings!

174
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,170
Hello.

175
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,260
Where are you guys?

176
00:08:52,590 --> 00:08:53,590
What should we do?

177
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,640
Do you think Ning is mad at us?

178
00:09:21,210 --> 00:09:22,740
Actually, I'm not thirsty.

179
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:34,140
Spit it out.

180
00:09:34,870 --> 00:09:35,900
Why on earth did you come

181
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,160
to my grandma's house?

182
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:42,140
We didn't mean to come here.

183
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:43,140
I was taking everyone

184
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:44,870
to visit my relatives.

185
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:47,870
-And then the car ran out of...
-Keep making things up.

186
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:49,710
Ning, you didn't reply to my messages.

187
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:51,350
We all really missed you.

188
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:52,380
Yeah.

189
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:53,380
We missed you so much.

190
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:54,990
Now the car is out of gas.

191
00:09:54,990 --> 00:09:55,500
Yeah.

192
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,030
It's stuck by the roadside.

193
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,380
So we...

194
00:09:59,110 --> 00:09:59,740
Right!

195
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,140
Our car is out of gas.

196
00:10:01,140 --> 00:10:02,740
-Can we stay at your...
-No.

197
00:10:03,590 --> 00:10:05,140
My grandma's home. It's not convenient.

198
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:06,110
Looks like tonight

199
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,770
we'll have to sleep in the car.

200
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:09,990
You silly child.

201
00:10:09,990 --> 00:10:11,590
They came all this way to see you.

202
00:10:11,590 --> 00:10:13,260
Just let them stay the night.

203
00:10:14,470 --> 00:10:15,620
Make yourselves at home.

204
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:16,680
All of you can stay.

205
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:17,740
Okay.

206
00:10:17,740 --> 00:10:18,710
Thank you.

207
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:20,620
Grandma!

208
00:10:22,110 --> 00:10:22,620
Oh no.

209
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:24,280
The stuff I prepared for Ning!

210
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:26,110
Here it is.

211
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:29,110
Shan, you're finally here.

212
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:33,140
Your dad called you so many times.

213
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:34,400
Why didn't you answer?

214
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:36,440
I didn't check my phone.

215
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:39,020
I...

216
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:39,780
Oh no.

217
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:42,120
My dad just told me to go back right now.

218
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:44,110
How about this?

219
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:45,620
I'll talk to your dad.

220
00:10:45,620 --> 00:10:47,470
I'll stay the night with you guys.

221
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:48,230
Great!

222
00:10:48,870 --> 00:10:50,380
Shan, you're the best!

223
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:52,040
I'll go with you to call my dad.

224
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:54,020
Ning.

225
00:11:20,870 --> 00:11:22,000
You're still awake?

226
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:33,190
Looking at the stars?

227
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:38,740
The stars here are so bright.

228
00:11:39,350 --> 00:11:40,260
Well,

229
00:11:40,740 --> 00:11:41,590
is it possible

230
00:11:41,590 --> 00:11:43,870
that the stars in the city
are actually bright too,

231
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,530
but the lights are too strong,

232
00:11:45,660 --> 00:11:46,870
so everyone just

233
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:49,460
overlooks the stars?

234
00:11:55,110 --> 00:11:56,440
Did you see my messages?

235
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:58,400
I got into Hailan University.

236
00:11:58,620 --> 00:11:59,420
How about you?

237
00:12:00,230 --> 00:12:01,290
Congratulations.

238
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:02,140
Me too.

239
00:12:03,020 --> 00:12:04,020
That's great.

240
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:05,380
Maybe we'll end up

241
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,400
in the same class,

242
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:07,790
or even the same dorm.

243
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:08,570
Yeah.

244
00:12:10,470 --> 00:12:12,740
How are you doing here?

245
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:14,890
If you need any help,

246
00:12:14,990 --> 00:12:15,920
just let us know.

247
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:18,130
I'm doing pretty well.

248
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:18,990
Really.

249
00:12:19,170 --> 00:12:21,260
Grandma runs a small business
in the village,

250
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:22,370
so I came to help out,

251
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:24,740
making some money to cover living expenses
and tuition later.

252
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:26,620
I'm gonna get a part-time job too
once I'm in college.

253
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:27,990
We can do it together

254
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:29,520
and look out for each other.

255
00:12:39,990 --> 00:12:40,620
Lan.

256
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:41,390
Yeah?

257
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:43,080
Actually, that day,

258
00:12:43,260 --> 00:12:45,190
I wanted to reply to your messages,

259
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:47,270
but I was afraid you'd worry about me,

260
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:48,630
so I didn't contact you.

261
00:12:50,620 --> 00:12:51,870
But I'm really glad

262
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:53,020
that you came to see me.

263
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:53,620
Thank you.

264
00:12:53,620 --> 00:12:54,870
It's nothing.

265
00:12:54,870 --> 00:12:56,020
We're good friends.

266
00:13:11,660 --> 00:13:13,120
That one is the brightest.

267
00:13:35,380 --> 00:13:36,440
I'm picking first.

268
00:13:48,380 --> 00:13:49,180
I'll take you.

269
00:13:49,260 --> 00:13:50,020
The trash in our greenhouse

270
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:50,740
needs to be collected.

271
00:13:50,740 --> 00:13:51,270
Let's go.

272
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:53,480
Take your time.

273
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:00,990
This girl is great.

274
00:14:00,990 --> 00:14:02,650
Come with me to herd the sheep.

275
00:14:07,210 --> 00:14:08,620
This girl is so sharp.

276
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:09,490
Come with me.

277
00:14:19,140 --> 00:14:21,140
My family doesn't need extra hands.

278
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:40,140
Where are they?

279
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:43,900
Well,

280
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:45,820
do you have a gym here?

281
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,620
Stop running!

282
00:14:56,620 --> 00:14:57,820
Why are you running?

283
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:01,140
Come out!

284
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,500
Stop running!

285
00:15:06,870 --> 00:15:08,230
Stop running!

286
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:11,620
Come here.

287
00:16:13,870 --> 00:16:14,660
I've got a popsicle for you.

288
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:15,790
It can cool you down.

289
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:17,490
Do you have a death wish?

290
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:18,650
Stop it!

291
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:20,130
I just fixed my hair!

292
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:22,870
Don't run!

293
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:24,270
If you've got the guts...

294
00:16:26,260 --> 00:16:27,540
What are you doing?

295
00:16:28,350 --> 00:16:29,110
No!

296
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:31,340
Stop messing around.

297
00:16:31,450 --> 00:16:32,620
I'm sorry!

298
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:34,990
I caught a cute little lamb!

299
00:16:37,260 --> 00:16:38,870
Her task is way too good.

300
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:40,270
I want to catch a lamb too!

301
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:50,880
Um...

302
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:55,370
What's wrong?

303
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:06,069
He is so young,

304
00:17:06,069 --> 00:17:07,099
yet so capable.

305
00:17:07,220 --> 00:17:08,420
And he's so handsome.

306
00:17:08,619 --> 00:17:10,619
He'll drive countless girls crazy.

307
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:11,550
Young man,

308
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:13,310
what do you do for work?

309
00:17:13,619 --> 00:17:15,030
I'm a luthier.

310
00:17:15,420 --> 00:17:15,940
A luthier?

311
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:16,460
A luthier?

312
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:17,030
What's a luthier?

313
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:17,869
A woodworker.

314
00:17:18,869 --> 00:17:19,420
Oh, I know that.

315
00:17:19,420 --> 00:17:20,310
That's a good job.

316
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:20,900
I know what a woodworker is.

317
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:21,550
Young man,

318
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:23,869
how about I set you up with someone?

319
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:25,790
Right.

320
00:17:25,790 --> 00:17:26,349
That's good.

321
00:17:26,349 --> 00:17:26,869
Young man,

322
00:17:26,869 --> 00:17:28,140
how many brothers do you have?

323
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:29,310
Have you bought a car?

324
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:30,140
Hey, quiet down.

325
00:17:30,140 --> 00:17:31,590
How much do you make a month?

326
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:32,870
Let me tell you.

327
00:17:33,140 --> 00:17:34,310
I have a daughter.

328
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:34,620
Lan.

329
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:35,140
Come here.

330
00:17:35,140 --> 00:17:35,620
Come.

331
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:36,900
Give me a hand.

332
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:39,140
Let me finish.

333
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:39,830
My daughter

334
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:40,460
is a teacher.

335
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:41,420
You two look

336
00:17:41,420 --> 00:17:42,590
perfect for each other.

337
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:43,590
Just say I'm your girlfriend.

338
00:17:43,590 --> 00:17:43,870
If you like her...

339
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:44,350
Right!

340
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:45,140
Sorry.

341
00:17:45,380 --> 00:17:45,940
Ladies,

342
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:47,270
I have a girlfriend.

343
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,940
-Really.
-You have a girlfriend?

344
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:50,140
Is it serious?

345
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:51,870
Isn't it obvious?

346
00:17:51,870 --> 00:17:53,920
His girlfriend is sitting right there.

347
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:54,940
Stop being so nosy.

348
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:55,790
Well...

349
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:57,790
Are you just saying that
because you're not

350
00:17:57,790 --> 00:17:59,310
interested in my daughter?

351
00:17:59,310 --> 00:17:59,700
No!

352
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,230
I really am his girlfriend.

353
00:18:02,070 --> 00:18:03,350
You've worked so hard.

354
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:05,640
You've worked so hard.

355
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:07,030
So clingy!

356
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:08,030
Come back.

357
00:18:15,550 --> 00:18:16,420
It's so heavy.

358
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:18,420
Lan.

359
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:19,550
Perfect timing.

360
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:20,750
Can you give me a hand?

361
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:22,900
Stop messing around.

362
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:26,240
Pass me the hammer.

363
00:18:36,870 --> 00:18:38,110
That young man's got it made.

364
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:38,620
That young man?

365
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:39,110
Yeah.

366
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:42,950
It looks serious.

367
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:44,830
Do you need to go to the hospital?

368
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:45,690
I'm fine.

369
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:47,780
It'll get better in a bit.

370
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:52,140
What were you

371
00:18:52,830 --> 00:18:54,690
talking about with Shan just now?

372
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:57,990
I was helping him out.

373
00:18:58,350 --> 00:18:59,280
Helping him out?

374
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,300
Didn't you see those ladies?

375
00:19:07,830 --> 00:19:08,590
What's wrong?

376
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:10,520
Why are you looking at me like that?

377
00:19:14,380 --> 00:19:15,940
Who is Shan's girlfriend?

378
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:17,550
Shan doesn't have a girlfriend.

379
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:18,620
What if he does?

380
00:19:18,790 --> 00:19:19,870
He doesn't.

381
00:19:20,110 --> 00:19:21,660
I know him well enough.

382
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:22,660
Are you that sure?

383
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:24,380
Yes.

384
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:31,380
Then do you know

385
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:33,220
